verses_with_numbers.text: And God called the light Day, and the darkness he called Night. And the evening and the morning were the FIRST DAY (1) .
And God called the firmament Heaven. And the evening and the morning were the SECOND DAY (2) .
# And God said, Let the waters under the heaven be gathered together unto ONE (1) place, and let the dry appear: and it was so.
And the evening and the morning were the THIRD DAY (3) .
And God made TWO (2) great lights; the greater light to rule the day, and the lesser light to rule the night: the stars also.
And the evening and the morning were the FOURTH DAY (4) .
And the evening and the morning were the FIFTH DAY (5) .
And God saw every thing that he had made, and, behold, very good. And the evening and the morning were the SIXTH DAY (6) .
And on the SEVENTH DAY (7) God ended his work which he had made; and he rested on the SEVENTH DAY (7) from all his work which he had made.
And God blessed the SEVENTH DAY (7) , and sanctified it: because that in it he had rested from all his work which God created and made.
And a river went out of Eden to water the garden; and from thence it was parted, and became into FOUR (4) heads.
The name of the FIRST (1) Pison: that it which compasseth the whole land of Havilah, where gold;
And the name of the SECOND (2) river Gihon: the same it that compasseth the whole land of Ethiopia.
And the name of the THIRD (3) river Hiddekel: that it which goeth toward the east of Assyria. And the FOURTH (4) river Euphrates.
And the LORD God caused a deep sleep to fall upon Adam, and he slept: and he took ONE (1) of his ribs, and closed up the flesh instead thereof;
Therefore shall a man leave his father and his mother, and shall cleave unto his wife: and they shall be ONE (1) flesh.
# And the LORD God said, Behold, the man is become as ONE (1) of us, to know good and evil: and now, lest he put forth his hand, and take also of the tree of life, and eat, and live for ever:

Behold, thou hast driven me out this day from the face of the earth; and from thy face shall I be hid; and I shall be a fugitive and a vagabond in the earth; and it shall come to pass, every ONE (1) that findeth me shall slay me.
# And Lamech took unto him TWO (2) wives: the name of the ONE (1) Adah, and the name of the other Zillah.
# And Adam lived an HUNDRED AND THIRTY (130) years, and begat in his own likeness, after his image; and called his name Seth:
And the days of Adam after he had begotten Seth were EIGHT HUNDRED (800) years: and he begat sons and daughters:
And all the days that Adam lived were NINE HUNDRED AND THIRTY (930) years: and he died.
And Seth lived an HUNDRED AND FIVE (105) years, and begat Enos:
And Seth lived after he begat Enos EIGHT HUNDRED AND SEVEN (807) years, and begat sons and daughters:
And all the days of Seth were NINE HUNDRED AND TWELVE (912) years: and he died.
And Enos lived after he begat Cainan EIGHT HUNDRED AND FIFTEEN (815) years, and begat sons and daughters:
And all the days of Enos were NINE HUNDRED AND FIVE (905) years: and he died.
And Cainan lived after he begat Mahalaleel EIGHT HUNDRED (800) and forty years, and begat sons and daughters:
And all the days of Cainan were NINE HUNDRED AND TEN (910) years: and he died.
# And Mahalaleel lived SIXTY (60) and FIVE (5) years, and begat Jared:
And Mahalaleel lived after he begat Jared EIGHT HUNDRED AND THIRTY (830) years, and begat sons and daughters:
And all the days of Mahalaleel were EIGHT HUNDRED (800) ninety and FIVE (5) years: and he died.
# And Jared lived an HUNDRED (100) SIXTY (60) and TWO (2) years, and he begat Enoch:
And Jared lived after he begat Enoch EIGHT HUNDRED (800) years, and begat sons and daughters:
And all the days of Jared were NINE HUNDRED SIXTY AND TWO (962) years: and he died.
# And Enoch lived SIXTY (60) and FIVE (5) years, and begat Methuselah:
And Enoch walked with God after he begat Methuselah THREE HUNDRED (300) years, and begat sons and daughters:
And all the days of Enoch were THREE HUNDRED SIXTY AND FIVE (365) years:
And Methuselah lived an HUNDRED EIGHTY AND SEVEN (187) years, and begat Lamech:
And Methuselah lived after he begat Lamech SEVEN HUNDRED EIGHTY AND TWO (782) years, and begat sons and daughters:
And all the days of Methuselah were NINE HUNDRED SIXTY AND NINE (969) years: and he died.
# And Lamech lived an HUNDRED EIGHTY AND TWO (182) years, and begat a son:
And Lamech lived after he begat Noah FIVE HUNDRED NINETY AND FIVE (595) years, and begat sons and daughters:
And all the days of Lamech were SEVEN HUNDRED SEVENTY AND SEVEN (777) years: and he died.
And Noah was FIVE HUNDRED (500) years old: and Noah begat Shem, Ham, and Japheth.
And the LORD said, My spirit shall not always strive with man, for that he also flesh: yet his days shall be an HUNDRED AND TWENTY (120) years.
And Noah begat THREE (3) sons, Shem, Ham, and Japheth.
And this which thou shalt make it : The length of the ark THREE HUNDRED (300) cubits, the breadth of it fifty cubits, and the height of it THIRTY (30) cubits.
A window shalt thou make to the ark, and in a cubit shalt thou finish it above; and the door of the ark shalt thou set in the side thereof; lower, SECOND (2) , and THIRD (3) shalt thou make it.
And of every living thing of all flesh, TWO (2) of every shalt thou bring into the ark, to keep alive with thee; they shall be male and female.
Of fowls after their kind, and of cattle after their kind, of every creeping thing of the earth after his kind, TWO (2) of every shall come unto thee, to keep alive.
Of every clean beast thou shalt take to thee by sevens, the male and his female: and of beasts that not clean by TWO (2) , the male and his female.
For yet SEVEN DAYS (7) , and I will cause it to rain upon the earth FORTY DAYS (40) and FORTY NIGHTS (40) ; and every living substance that I have made will I destroy from off the face of the earth.
And Noah SIX HUNDRED (600) years old when the flood of waters was upon the earth.
There went in TWO (2) and TWO (2) unto Noah into the ark, the male and the female, as God had commanded Noah.
And it came to pass after SEVEN DAYS (7) , that the waters of the flood were upon the earth.

# In the SIX (6) HUNDREDTH (100) year of Noah's life, in the SECOND MONTH (2) , the SEVENTEENTH DAY (17) of the month, the same day were all the fountains of the great deep broken up, and the windows of heaven were opened.
And the rain was upon the earth FORTY DAYS (40) and FORTY NIGHTS (40) .
In the selfsame day entered Noah, and Shem, and Ham, and Japheth, the sons of Noah, and Noah's wife, and the THREE (3) wives of his sons with them, into the ark;
And they went in unto Noah into the ark, TWO (2) and TWO (2) of all flesh, wherein the breath of life.
And the flood was FORTY DAYS (40) upon the earth; and the waters increased, and bare up the ark, and it was lift up above the earth.
FIFTEEN (15) cubits upward did the waters prevail; and the mountains were covered.
And the waters prevailed upon the earth an HUNDRED AND FIFTY (150) days.
And the waters returned from off the earth continually: and after the end of the HUNDRED AND FIFTY (150) days the waters were abated.
And the ark rested in the SEVENTH MONTH (7) , on the SEVENTEENTH DAY (17) of the month, upon the mountains of Ararat.
And the waters decreased continually until the TENTH MONTH (10) : in the TENTH (10) , on the FIRST (1) of the month, were the tops of the mountains seen.
# And it came to pass at the end of FORTY DAYS (40) , that Noah opened the window of the ark which he had made:
And he stayed yet other SEVEN DAYS (7) ; and again he sent forth the dove out of the ark;
And he stayed yet other SEVEN DAYS (7) ; and sent forth the dove; which returned not again unto him any more.

# And it came to pass in the SIX HUNDREDTH AND FIRST (601) year, in the FIRST (1) , the FIRST (1) of the month, the waters were dried up from off the earth: and Noah removed the covering of the ark, and looked, and, behold, the face of the ground was dry.
And in the SECOND MONTH (2) , on the SEVEN AND TWENTIETH DAY (27) of the month, was the earth dried.
These the THREE (3) sons of Noah: and of them was the whole earth overspread.
And Ham, the father of Canaan, saw the nakedness of his father, and told his TWO (2) brethren without.
# And Noah lived after the flood THREE HUNDRED AND FIFTY (350) years.
And all the days of Noah were NINE HUNDRED AND FIFTY (950) years: and he died.
By these were the isles of the Gentiles divided in their lands; every ONE (1) after his tongue, after their families, in their nations.
And Cush begat Nimrod: he began to be a mighty ONE (1) in the earth.
And unto Eber were born TWO (2) sons: the name of ONE (1) Peleg; for in his days was the earth divided; and his brother's name Joktan.
And the whole earth was of ONE (1) language, and of ONE (1) speech.
And they said ONE (1) to another, Go to, let us make brick, and burn them throughly. And they had brick for stone, and slime had they for morter.
And the LORD said, Behold, the people ONE (1) , and they have all ONE (1) language; and this they begin to do: and now nothing will be restrained from them, which they have imagined to do.
Go to, let us go down, and there confound their language, that they may not understand ONE (1) another's speech.

And Shem lived after he begat Arphaxad FIVE HUNDRED (500) years, and begat sons and daughters.
And Arphaxad lived FIVE AND THIRTY (35) years, and begat Salah:
And Arphaxad lived after he begat Salah FOUR HUNDRED AND THREE (403) years, and begat sons and daughters.
And Salah lived THIRTY (30) years, and begat Eber:
And Salah lived after he begat Eber FOUR HUNDRED AND THREE (403) years, and begat sons and daughters.
And Eber lived FOUR AND THIRTY (34) years, and begat Peleg:
And Eber lived after he begat Peleg FOUR HUNDRED AND THIRTY (430) years, and begat sons and daughters.

And Peleg lived after he begat Reu TWO HUNDRED AND NINE (209) years, and begat sons and daughters.

And Reu lived after he begat Serug TWO HUNDRED AND SEVEN (207) years, and begat sons and daughters.

And Serug lived after he begat Nahor TWO HUNDRED (200) years, and begat sons and daughters.

So Abram departed, as the LORD had spoken unto him; and Lot went with him: and Abram seventy and FIVE (5) years old when he departed out of Haran.
Unto the place of the altar, which he had made there at the FIRST (1) : and there Abram called on the name of the LORD.
Then Lot chose him all the plain of Jordan; and Lot journeyed east: and they separated themselves the ONE (1) from the other.
TWELVE (12) years they served Chedorlaomer, and in the THIRTEENTH (13) year they rebelled.
And in the FOURTEENTH (14) year came Chedorlaomer, and the kings that with him, and smote the Rephaims in Ashteroth Karnaim, and the Zuzims in Ham, and the Emims in Shaveh Kiriathaim,
With Chedorlaomer the king of Elam, and with Tidal king of nations, and Amraphel king of Shinar, and Arioch king of Ellasar; FOUR (4) kings with FIVE (5) .

And when Abram heard that his brother was taken captive, he armed his trained , born in his own house, THREE HUNDRED AND EIGHTEEN (318) , and pursued unto Dan.
And Abram said, Behold, to me thou hast given no seed: and, lo, ONE (1) born in my house is mine heir.
And he said unto him, Take me an heifer of THREE (3) years old, and a she goat of THREE (3) years old, and a ram of THREE (3) years old, and a turtledove, and a young pigeon.
And he took unto him all these, and divided them in the midst, and laid each piece ONE (1) against another: but the birds divided he not.
And he said unto Abram, Know of a surety that thy seed shall be a stranger in a land not their's, and shall serve them; and they shall afflict them FOUR HUNDRED (400) years;

And Sarai Abram's wife took Hagar her maid the Egyptian, after Abram had dwelt TEN (10) years in the land of Canaan, and gave her to her husband Abram to be his wife.
And Abram FOURSCORE AND SIX (86) years old, when Hagar bare Ishmael to Abram.
And when Abram was ninety years old and NINE (9) , the LORD appeared to Abram, and said unto him, I the Almighty God; walk before me, and be thou perfect.
And he that is EIGHT DAYS (8) old shall be circumcised among you, every man child in your generations, he that is born in the house, or bought with money of any stranger, which not of thy seed.
Then Abraham fell upon his face, and laughed, and said in his heart, Shall be born unto him that is an HUNDRED (100) years old? and shall Sarah, that is ninety years old, bear?

And as for Ishmael, I have heard thee: Behold, I have blessed him, and will make him fruitful, and will multiply him exceedingly; TWELVE (12) princes shall he beget, and I will make him a great nation.
And Abraham ninety years old and NINE (9) , when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.

And they said, Stand back. And they said , This ONE (1) came in to sojourn, and he will needs be a judge: now will we deal worse with thee, than with them. And they pressed sore upon the man, Lot, and came near to break the door.

And Lot went out, and spake unto his sons in law, which married his daughters, and said, Up, get you out of this place; for the LORD will destroy this city. But he seemed as ONE (1) that mocked unto his sons in law.
# And when the morning arose, then the angels hastened Lot, saying, Arise, take thy wife, and thy TWO (2) daughters, which are here; lest thou be consumed in the iniquity of the city.

And while he lingered, the men laid hold upon his hand, and upon the hand of his wife, and upon the hand of his TWO (2) daughters; the LORD being merciful unto him: and they brought him forth, and set him without the city.

# And Lot went up out of Zoar, and dwelt in the mountain, and his TWO (2) daughters with him; for he feared to dwell in Zoar: and he dwelt in a cave, he and his TWO (2) daughters.

And he said, For SEVEN (7) ewe lambs shalt thou take of my hand, that they may be a witness unto me, that I have digged this well.

And he said, Take now thy son, thine only Isaac, whom thou lovest, and get thee into the land of Moriah; and offer him there for a burnt offering upon ONE (1) of the mountains which I will tell thee of.

And Abraham rose up early in the morning, and saddled his ass, and took TWO (2) of his young men with him, and Isaac his son, and clave the wood for the burnt offering, and rose up, and went unto the place of which God had told him.
Then on the THIRD DAY (3) Abraham lifted up his eyes, and saw the place afar off.

And these the days of the years of Abraham's life which he lived, an HUNDRED THREESCORE AND FIFTEEN (175) years.

And these the years of the life of Ishmael, an HUNDRED AND THIRTY AND SEVEN (137) years: and he gave up the ghost and died; and was gathered unto his people.

And if she be not able to bring a lamb, then she shall bring TWO (2) turtles, or TWO (2) young pigeons; the ONE (1) for the burnt offering, and the other for a sin offering: and the priest shall make an atonement for her, and she shall be clean.

When a man shall have in the skin of his flesh a rising, a scab, or bright spot, and it be in the skin of his flesh the plague of leprosy; then he shall be brought unto Aaron the priest, or unto ONE (1) of his sons the priests:
If the bright spot white in the skin of his flesh, and in sight not deeper than the skin, and the hair thereof be not turned white; then the priest shall shut up the plague SEVEN DAYS (7) :
And the priest shall look on him the SEVENTH DAY (7) : and, behold, the plague in his sight be at a stay, the plague spread not in the skin; then the priest shall shut him up SEVEN DAYS (7) more:

And the priest shall look on him again the SEVENTH DAY (7) : and, behold, the plague somewhat dark, the plague spread not in the skin, the priest shall pronounce him clean: it a scab: and he shall wash his clothes, and be clean.
But if the priest look on it, and, behold, no white hairs therein, and it not lower than the skin, but somewhat dark; then the priest shall shut him up SEVEN DAYS (7) :
But if the priest look on it, and, behold, no white hair in the bright spot, and it no lower than the skin, but somewhat dark; then the priest shall shut him up SEVEN DAYS (7) :
And the priest shall look upon him the SEVENTH DAY (7) : if it be spread much abroad in the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him unclean: it the plague of leprosy.
And if the priest look on the plague of the scall, and, behold, it not in sight deeper than the skin, and no black hair in it; then the priest shall shut up the plague of the scall SEVEN DAYS (7) :
And in the SEVENTH DAY (7) the priest shall look on the plague: and, behold, the scall spread not, and there be in it no yellow hair, and the scall not in sight deeper than the skin;

And in the SEVENTH DAY (7) the priest shall look on the scall: and, behold, the scall be not spread in the skin, nor in sight deeper than the skin; then the priest shall pronounce him clean: and he shall wash his clothes, and be clean.

And the garment, either warp, or woof, or whatsoever thing of skin , which thou shalt wash, if the plague be departed from them, then it shall be washed the SECOND (2) time, and shall be clean.
Then shall the priest command to take for him that is to be cleansed TWO (2) birds alive clean, and cedar wood, and scarlet, and hyssop:

And he shall sprinkle upon him that is to be cleansed from the leprosy SEVEN (7) times, and shall pronounce him clean, and shall let the living bird loose into the open field.

And he that is to be cleansed shall wash his clothes, and shave off all his hair, and wash himself in water, that he may be clean: and after that he shall come into the camp, and shall tarry abroad out of his tent SEVEN DAYS (7) .

But it shall be on the SEVENTH DAY (7) , that he shall shave all his hair off his head and his beard and his eyebrows, even all his hair he shall shave off: and he shall wash his clothes, also he shall wash his flesh in water, and he shall be clean.

And the priest shall dip his right finger in the oil that in his left hand, and shall sprinkle of the oil with his finger SEVEN (7) times before the LORD:

And if he poor, and cannot get so much; then he shall take ONE (1) lamb a trespass offering to be waved, to make an atonement for him, and ONE (1) TENTH (10) deal of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering, and a log of oil;

such as he is able to get, the ONE (1) a sin offering, and the other a burnt offering, with the meat offering: and the priest shall make an atonement for him that is to be cleansed before the LORD.
